      "question": "What is the key design idea behind Hateful Memes?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "In most cases, either the image alone or the text alone is enough for correct classification.",
        "Changing one modality can flip the label, so the model is forced to use both the image and the text.",
        "The benchmark removes text entirely to focus on vision.",
        "It measures only the ability to generate new images from meme inputs."
      ],
      "answer_index": 1,
      "explanation": "Hateful Memes is built so that the relationship between image and text determines the label. Looking at only one modality is often insufficient, so the dataset forces the model to reason across both sources.",
